    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm seeing a 500 error on our `/api/v1/checkout/complete` endpoint. It seems intermittent but happens mostly during peak traffic. Here's a snippet from the production logs:\n\n`[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: RequestID: 8829-ax-92 - Internal Server Error - Connection timeout to downstream service: payment-gateway-auth`\n`[2023-10-27 14:22:05] WARN: Retrying connection to payment-gateway-auth... (Attempt 1/3)`\n`[2023-10-27 14:22:15] ERROR: RequestID: 8829-ax-92 - Critical failure: Upstream service unavailable or timed out after 10000ms`\n\nCan you help me figure out what might be causing this? It's not consistently failing the same way.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The 500 error, a critical failure, and a connection timeout to a downstream service, all point towards a problem with communication between your service and the payment gateway-auth service. It's likely that the payment gateway-auth service is experiencing congestion, overload, or a temporary network issue, causing your service to timeout. You might want to consider implementing circuit breakers to prevent your service from retrying the same failed requests repeatedly, which could lead to a denial-of-service (DoS) attack. This will help prevent your service from becoming overwhelmed and allow it to recover more quickly from these intermittent failures.",
      "source": "target",
