      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I've checked the network stats and everything looks relatively normal on our end. No obvious packet loss or router flapping. It's just so bizarre how it behaves. One minute everything is lightning fast, then suddenly the connection just dies for no apparent reason, like something is jumping in and cutting the wire. \n\nSince the infra looks okay, do you think it could be something logic-based in the way our requests are being handled, or maybe some kind of race condition that only triggers when certain load thresholds are hit?",
